description:
What is living intelligent faith? Why don’t we trust God? In Randy Skeete's thought-provoking sermon delves into why faith is not blind. He begins by referencing the Pool of Bethesda, where Jesus asked, "Would thou be made whole?" and emphasized the importance of rising, taking up one's bed, and walking as an act of faith. 
He highlights the need to trust God in various circumstances, drawing lessons from biblical stories and nature. He emphasizes the role of faith in the face of doubt, sin, and fear and the importance of relying on God's Word, not doubting His promises. His message inspires us to recall evidence of God's interventions in the past, emphasizing that we can trust Him implicitly in the future!
